      • createAdhocQueryResponse

        public EbXMLQueryResponse21 createAdhocQueryResponse(EbXMLObjectLibrary objectLibrary,
                                            boolean returnsObjectRefs)
        Description copied from interface: EbXMLFactory
        Creates a new response for a query request.
        Specified by:
        createAdhocQueryResponse in interface EbXMLFactory
        Parameters:
        objectLibrary - the object library to use.
        returnsObjectRefs - true if the response is meant to return object references instead of the real objects. This parameter should be true to ensure that an object library is not included in the query result contains ObjectRefs. Those ObjectRefs cannot be distinguished from the ObjectRefs of the object library and therefore the object library would produce unwanted query results.
        Returns:
        the created object.
